<TITLE> PM for recovering lakes in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 21 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has ordered the authorities concerned to take necessary steps to recover lakes and water bodies in the capital. The premier was speaking at the inauguration of a residential project in Dhaka on Wednesday. Rajuk (Dhaka development authority) is constructing 260 multi-storey buildings with 22,512 flats for low and middle income people at Uttara. The apartments with a floor space between 1050 and 1250 square feet will be sold or rented out. Estimated cost for the project is Tk 8,625.794 crore and is expected to be completed by 2015. The PM ordered recovering the water bodies to make the Dhaka more liveable. She also added that steps had been taken for beautification of Gulshan and Banani lakes to improve the environment of the city for a healthier lifestyle. She said that residential facilities would be extended to rural areas too. bdnews24.c
